    <stitle>DT/DTI-466 A and B Series DT/DTI/DTA-466 C Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1993) - ENGINE DIAGNOSTIC TOOLS -
        KENT-MOORE TACH-N-TIME DYNAMIC TIMING METER (ZTSE-4142)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>KENT-MOORE TACH-N-TIME DYNAMIC TIMING METER (ZTSE-4142)</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>The ZTSE-4142 TACH-N-TIME from Kent-Moore (Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef4500409">4.9</hotlnk>) uses the latest in microprocessor technology to quickly and
                accurately measure fuel injection pump timing.
            </para>
            <para>The pump pulse is picked up by a piezoelectric transducer that clamps on the #1 or #6 fuel outlet.
            </para>
            <para>Crankshaft location is picked up with a timing light.</para>
            <para>Using the pump pulse signal and the crankshaft location signal, a microprocessor gives a digital
                display of exact engine RPM and injection pump timing in degrees.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4500409" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12448" filename="../figcg1/CG12448.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.9 TACH-N-TIME INSTRUMENT (ZTSE-4142)</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
